	</form></div><span class="pb doctop" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-01-02-pb-0026">26<a style="padding-left: 5px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-01/ADMS-06-01-02-pb-0026.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a></span><div id="PJA01d017" class="doc letter">

    <h1>To John Wentworth</h1>
    
    <div class="docbody">
     <div class="opener">
      <table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Old Friend</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">
       [<ins title="editorial addition or explanation" class="ed">October? 1758</ins>]<a class="ptr" href="#PJA01d017n1" id="PJA01d017n1-ptr">1</a>
      </td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
     </div>
     <p>I resume with Pleasure my long neglected Pen upon this opportunity by Mr. Belcher to inform you that I am still alive, and well; that I am removed from Worcester to Braintree where I expect to live and die; and altho I have for a long time neglected to write you, I have never forgot to think frequently of you and to wish you all the Happiness that you deserve; no small Quantity truly!</p>
     <p>The perpetual rotation of things in this world is such that we are obliged by shifting our theatre of action frequently to shift our Friends, to drop at once a whole Company yet we loved like our own souls and to contract with a sett entirely new.Thus when I left this Place I left behind me one Sett of friends, and by removing to Cambridge acquired a new one, a sett that no accident will ever be able to make me forget, altho by removing from that place to Worcester I was (with Pain enough) seperated from them. Now I have been obliged to leave behind me at Worcester another sett with whom I have spent many agreeable Hours, and whom I sincerely esteem, and am now returned to the same goal from which [<span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">seven</span>]<a class="ptr" href="#PJA01d017n2" id="PJA01d017n2-ptr">2</a> years ago, I departed, and the wheel begins to roll anew.Whether I shall ever remove again I know not, and dont much care, but whether here or elsewhere I shall always love my Friends old and new, and shall wish sincerely for a resumption, and an endless continuation of that Correspondence with you which was, while it lasted, one of the most considerable pleasures of my life.</p>
     <p>Pray write me, as soon as you can, and let me know how you live, whether you are married or about it, or whether you intend to continue a Batchelor,for my part, you know, that Woman never fell within my Scheme of Happiness, altho the world tells me I am over head and ears in love.<a class="ptr" href="#PJA01d017n3" id="PJA01d017n3-ptr">3</a> Whether I am or not, I sincerely dont know. Whenever I do I will tell you, but I am afraid you must wait till dooms day for information. In the mean time I remain with sincerity, Your Friend,</p>
     <div class="closer">
      <p class="signed">John Adams</p>
     </div>
    </div>
    <div class="docback">
     <div class="note-source" id="PJA01d017sn1">
      
   <p>
       <span class="docSource"><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ manuscript ]">MS</abbr> not found. <span class="dType">Reprinted</span> from  (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[  &lt;i&gt;New England Historical and Genealogical Register.&lt;/i&gt;  ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">NEHGR</span></span>, 5:414/6 (Oct. 1851)), where the provenance of this letter is given in detail; see descriptive note on <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> to Wentworth, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-01-02-0012" class="document">12 April</a>, above.</span>
      </p>

     </div>
     <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA01d017n1-ptr" id="PJA01d017n1">1</a>
      
   <p>Editorial note in <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[  &lt;i&gt;New England Historical and Genealogical Register.&lt;/i&gt;  ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">NEHGR</span></span>: The top of this letter was torn close to the reading matter, and this accounts for there being no date. The date can be <span class="pb" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-01-02-pb-0027">[27<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-01/ADMS-06-01-02-pb-0027.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>quite confidently assigned as Oct. 1758 because early in that month <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> returned from Worcester and set up his law office in Braintree. See, however, the <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-01-02-0016" class="document">following letter</a> (caption entry).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA01d017n2-ptr" id="PJA01d017n2">2</a>
      
   <p>Brackets and italics in <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[  &lt;i&gt;New England Historical and Genealogical Register.&lt;/i&gt;  ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">NEHGR</span></span> text.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA01d017n3-ptr" id="PJA01d017n3">3</a>
      
   <p>Conceivably this could be a reference to <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s flirtation with Hannah Quincy, although the earliest reference in the <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Diary and Autobiography of John Adams&lt;/i&gt;, ed. L. H. Butterfield and others, Cambridge, 1961; 4 vols. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Diary and Autobiography</span></span> to Hannah appears in Jan. 1759 (<a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-01-01-02-0003-0003-0008%20ADMS-print-01-01-02-0004-0001-0001#ADMS-01-01-02-pb-0066" class="pageNo">1:6669</a>).</p>

     </div>
